wwpPortStatsMIB.name: wwpPortStatsMIB
wwpPortStatsMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpPortStatsMIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP Port ether Stats.

wwpPortStatsReset.name: wwpPortStatsReset
wwpPortStatsReset.description: To reset the counters related to this port. A read on this object will always return the 'none'.

wwpPortStatsTable.name: wwpPortStatsTable
wwpPortStatsTable.description: The table specifying the stats for the ports.

wwpPortStatsEntry.name: wwpPortStatsEntry
wwpPortStatsEntry.description: An entry in the port stats table.

wwpPortStatsPortId.name: wwpPortStatsPortId
wwpPortStatsPortId.description: The Id of the port for which this entry contains the stats.

wwpPortStatsRxBytes.name: wwpPortStatsRxBytes
wwpPortStatsRxBytes.description: The number of bytes received by this port.

wwpPortStatsRxPkts.name: wwpPortStatsRxPkts
wwpPortStatsRxPkts.description: The number of packets received by this port.

wwpPortStatsRxCrcErrorPkts.name: wwpPortStatsRxCrcErrorPkts
wwpPortStatsRxCrcErrorPkts.description: The number of packets received with CRC errors by this port.

wwpPortStatsRxBcastPkts.name: wwpPortStatsRxBcastPkts
wwpPortStatsRxBcastPkts.description: The number of Broadcast packets received by this port.

wwpPortStatsUndersizePkts.name: wwpPortStatsUndersizePkts
wwpPortStatsUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

wwpPortStatsOversizePkts.name: wwpPortStatsOversizePkts
wwpPortStatsOversizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

wwpPortStatsFragmentPkts.name: wwpPortStatsFragmentPkts
wwpPortStatsFragmentPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

wwpPortStatsJabberPkts.name: wwpPortStatsJabberPkts
wwpPortStatsJabberPkts.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets), and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

wwpPortStats64BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats64BytePkts
wwpPortStats64BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStats65To127BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats65To127BytePkts
wwpPortStats65To127BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStats128To255BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats128To255BytePkts
wwpPortStats128To255BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStats256To511BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats256To511BytePkts
wwpPortStats256To511BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStats512To1023BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats512To1023BytePkts
wwpPortStats512To1023BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStats1024To1518BytePkts.name: wwpPortStats1024To1518BytePkts
wwpPortStats1024To1518BytePkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

wwpPortStatsTxBytes.name: wwpPortStatsTxBytes
wwpPortStatsTxBytes.description: The number of Octets transmitted for this port.

wwpPortStatsTxTBytes.name: wwpPortStatsTxTBytes
wwpPortStatsTxTBytes.description: The total number of Octets transmitted for this port.

wwpPortStatsTxPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxPkts
wwpPortStatsTxPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted for this port.

wwpPortStatsTxExDeferPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxExDeferPkts
wwpPortStatsTxExDeferPkts.description: The transmit excessive defer packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxGiantPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxGiantPkts
wwpPortStatsTxGiantPkts.description: The transmit too big packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxUnderRunPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxUnderRunPkts
wwpPortStatsTxUnderRunPkts.description: The transmit underrun packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxCrcErrorPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxCrcErrorPkts
wwpPortStatsTxCrcErrorPkts.description: The transmit CRC error packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxLCheckErrorPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxLCheckErrorPkts
wwpPortStatsTxLCheckErrorPkts.description: The transmit length check error packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxLOutRangePkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxLOutRangePkts
wwpPortStatsTxLOutRangePkts.description: The transmit length out of range packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxLateCollPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxLateCollPkts
wwpPortStatsTxLateCollPkts.description: The transmit late collision packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxExCollPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxExCollPkts
wwpPortStatsTxExCollPkts.description: The transmit excessive collision packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxSingleCollPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxSingleCollPkts
wwpPortStatsTxSingleCollPkts.description: The transmit single collision packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsTxCollPkts.name: wwpPortStatsTxCollPkts
wwpPortStatsTxCollPkts.description: The transmit collision packet count for a port.

wwpPortStatsXTable.name: wwpPortStatsXTable
wwpPortStatsXTable.description: The table extending the stats for the ports to 64 bits.

wwpPortStatsXEntry.name: wwpPortStatsXEntry
wwpPortStatsXEntry.description: An entry in the port stats extension table.

wwpPortStatsXRxBytes.name: wwpPortStatsXRxBytes
wwpPortStatsXRxBytes.description: The number of bytes received by this port.

wwpPortStatsXRxPkts.name: wwpPortStatsXRxPkts
wwpPortStatsXRxPkts.description: The number of packets received by this port.

wwpPortStatsXTxBytes.name: wwpPortStatsXTxBytes
wwpPortStatsXTxBytes.description: The total number of Bytes transmitted for this port.

wwpPortStatsXTxPkts.name: wwpPortStatsXTxPkts
wwpPortStatsXTxPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted for this port.

wwpPortStatsPortalTable.name: wwpPortStatsPortalTable
wwpPortStatsPortalTable.description: The table extending the statistic counters for the ports to 64 bits.

wwpPortStatsPortalEntry.name: wwpPortStatsPortalEntry
wwpPortStatsPortalEntry.description: An entry in the port stats extension table.

wwpPortStatsPortalPortId.name: wwpPortStatsPortalPortId
wwpPortStatsPortalPortId.description: The Id of the port for which this entry contains the stats.

wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentHi
wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentHi.description: The number of bytes sent from this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentLo
wwpPortStatsPortalBytesSentLo.description: The number of bytes sent from this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlHi
wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlHi.description: The number of Flow Control frames sent from this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlLo
wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlLo.description: The number of Flow Control frames sent from this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentHi
wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentHi.description: The number of Unicast Frames sent from this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentLo
wwpPortStatsPortalUnicastFramesSentLo.description: The number of Unicast Frames sent from this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorHi
wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorHi.description: A count of frames that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. This counter is incremented when the Receive-Status is reported as Alignment-Error. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorLo
wwpPortStatsPortalAlignmentErrorLo.description: The number of frames that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. This counter is incremented when the Receive-Status is reported as Alignment-Error. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentHi
wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentHi.description: The number of non-unicast frames sent from this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentLo
wwpPortStatsPortalNonUnicastFramesSentLo.description: The number of non-unicast frames sent from this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedHi
wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedHi.description: The total number of bytes recieved on this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedLo
wwpPortStatsPortalTotalBytesRecievedLo.description: The total number of bytes recieved on this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecie.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecievedHi
wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecie.description: The number of flow control frames recieved. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecie.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecievedLo
wwpPortStatsPortalFlowControlFramesRecie.description: The number of flow control frames recieved. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedHi
wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedHi.description: The total number of frames recieved on this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedLo
wwpPortStatsPortalTotalFramesRecievedLo.description: The total number of frames recieved on this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecieve.name: wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecievedHi
wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecieve.description: The number of broadcast frames recieved on this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecieve.name: wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecievedLo
wwpPortStatsPortalBroadcastFramesRecieve.description: The number of broadcast frames recieved on this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecieve.name: wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecievedHi
wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecieve.description: The number of multicast frames recieved on this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecieve.name: wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecievedLo
wwpPortStatsPortalMulticastFramesRecieve.description: The number of multicast frames recieved on this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesHi.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets), and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortalJabberFramesLo.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets), and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortal64ByteFramesLo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortal65To127ByteFramesLo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortal256To511ByteFramesLo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortal128To255ByteFramesLo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 1024 and 1528 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortal1024To1528ByteFramesLo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 1024 and 1528 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFramesHi.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFrameslo.name: wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFrameslo
wwpPortStatsPortal512To1023ByteFrameslo.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentHi
wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentHi.description: The number of fragmented frames recieved by this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentLo
wwpPortStatsPortalFragmentLo.description: The number of fragmented frames recieved by this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesHi.description: The number of undersized frames recieved by this port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortalUndersizeFramesLo.description: The number of undersized frames recieved by this port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventHi
wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventHi.description: Short event counter. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventLo
wwpPortStatsPortalShortEventLo.description: Short event counter. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalCRCHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalCRCHi
wwpPortStatsPortalCRCHi.description: The number of CRC error frames recieved by a given port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalCRCLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalCRCLo
wwpPortStatsPortalCRCLo.description: The number of CRC error frames recieved by a given port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesHi
wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesHi.description: The number of frames dropped by a given port. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesLo
wwpPortStatsPortalDroppedFramesLo.description: The number of frames dropped by a given port. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionHi
wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionHi.description: The number of frames that are involved in a collision. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionLo
wwpPortStatsPortalCollisionLo.description: The number of frames that are involved in a collision. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionHi
wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionHi.description: A count of the times that a collision has been detected later than 512 bit times into the transmitted packet. A late collision is counted twice, i.e., both as a collision and as a late-collision. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionLo
wwpPortStatsPortalLateCollisionLo.description: A count of the times that a collision has been detected later than 512 bit times into the transmitted packet. A late collision is counted twice, i.e., both as a collision and as a late-collision. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterHi.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterHi
wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterHi.description: Filtering counter. This element represents the upper 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.

wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterLo.name: wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterLo
wwpPortStatsPortalFilteringCounterLo.description: Filtering counter. This element represents the lower 32-bits of a 64-bit counter.
